                `
                Title: Good for agricultural biodiversity
                Subtitle: Contains a neglected or underutilized crop : grass pea
                Did you know?
                Since 1900, 75% of plant diversity has been lost as farmers around the world have abandoned local varieties for high-yielding varieties adapted to mass industrial processing. As a result, 60 % of human energy intake in the world comes from 3 species: wheat, rice and corn.
                https://www.fao.org/4/y5609e/y5609e02.htm 
                What you can do
                Consuming diverse cereals, legumes, vegetables and fruits contributes to:
                preserving neglected and underutilized species
                rural development and support of local farmers and companies
                preserving of diversified landscapes
                food security
                and your health!
